    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADA-BRAZIL TECHNOLOGY DEAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Canadian electronics hardware manufacturer Celestica purchases NEC's Brazilian manufacturing facility, which produces telecommunications and Internet equipment, for $1.2 billion (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Celestica, a Canadian electronics hardware manufacturer, purchased an equipment plant in Brazil for $1.2 billion from NEC of Japan as part of a five-year supply deal. Celestica will take over the plant, which produces telecommunications and Internet equipment for the Latin American market, while continuing to supply NEC's Brazilian subsidiary.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
